[30;1m326 | [0m[35mclass Password(_FederatedSaml):[0m
[30;1m327 | [0m[35m    r"""Implement authentication plugin for SAML2 protocol.[0m
[30;1m328 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m329 | [0m[35m    ECP stands for `Enhanced Client or Proxy` and is a SAML2 extension[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m19[0m[34m of [0m[33m2148[0m[31m ]--[0m
   Rule Id: [34mBD000701[0m
       Tag: [34mSecurity.Backdoor.DataExfiltration.Token[0m
  Severity: [36mImportant[0m, Confidence: [36mHigh[0m
  Filename: [33m/keystoneauth1-5.10.0/keystoneauth1/extras/_saml2/v3/saml2.py[0m
   Pattern: [32m(npm owner|password|htpasswd|auth_?token|secret_?key|private_?key|authorized_keys?|npmrc|\.ssh|usersecrets?|api_?keys|nuget\.config|\.identityservice)[0m
[30;1m108 | [0m[35m        ECP extension enabled. The content sent is a header removed SOAP[0m
[30;1m109 | [0m[35m        message returned from the Service Provider. It's also worth noting[0m
[30;1m110 | [0m[35m        that ECP extension to the SAML2 doesn't define authentication method.[0m
[30;1m111 | [0m[35m        The most popular is HttpBasicAuth with just user and password.[0m
[30;1m112 | [0m[35m        Other possibilities could be X509 certificates or Kerberos.[0m
[30;1m113 | [0m[35m        Upon successful authentication the user should receive a SAML2[0m
[30;1m114 | [0m[35m        assertion.[0m

[30;1m503 | [0m[35mLoading Plugins by Name[0m
[30;1m504 | [0m[35m=======================[0m
[30;1m505 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m506 | [0m[35mIn auth_token middleware and for some service to service communication it is[0m
[30;1m507 | [0m[35mpossible to specify a plugin to load via name. The authentication options that[0m
[30;1m508 | [0m[35mare available are then specific to the plugin that you specified. Currently the[0m
[30;1m509 | [0m[35mauthentication plugins that are available in `keystoneauth` are:[0m

[30;1m397 | [0m[35mthat support application credential authentication. Since application[0m

[30;1m127 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m128 | [0m[35mV3 identity plugins must use an `auth_url` that points to the root of a V3[0m
[30;1m129 | [0m[35midentity server URL, i.e.: ``http://hostname:5000/v3``.[0m

[30;1m365 | [0m[35m``get_endpoint_data`` makes use of the same cache as the rest of the discovery[0m
[30;1m366 | [0m[35mprocess, so calling it should incur no undue expense. By default it will make[0m
[30;1m367 | [0m[35mat least one version discovery call so that it can fetch microversion metadata.[0m
[30;1m368 | [0m[35mIf the user knows a service does not support microversions and is merely[0m
[30;1m369 | [0m[35mcurious as to which major version was discovered, ``discover_versions`` can be[0m

[30;1m3 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m4 | [0m[35mKeystoneauth provides a standard way to do authentication and service requests[0m
[30;1m5 | [0m[35mwithin the OpenStack ecosystem. It is designed for use in conjunction with the[0m
[30;1m6 | [0m[35mexisting OpenStack clients and for simplifying the process of writing new[0m
[30;1m7 | [0m[35mclients.[0m

[30;1m18 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m19 | [0m[35mIn keystoneclient auth plugin loading is managed by the class itself. This[0m
[30;1m20 | [0m[35mmethod proved useful in allowing the plugin to control the way it was loaded[0m

[30;1m23 | [0m[35mIn keystoneauth this has been severed and the auth plugin is handled separately[0m

[30;1m3 | [0m[35m  - A new flag `allow_version_hack` was added to identity plugins and the[0m
[30;1m4 | [0m[35m    adapter which will allow a client to opt out of making guesses at the[0m
[30;1m5 | [0m[35m    version url page of a service. This means that if a deployment is[0m
[30;1m6 | [0m[35m    misconfigured and the service catalog contains a versioned endpoint that[0m
[30;1m7 | [0m[35m    does not match the requested version the request will fail. This will be[0m
[30;1m8 | [0m[35m    useful in beginning to require correctly deployed catalogs rather than[0m
[30;1m9 | [0m[35m    continue to hide the problem.[0m
